    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: PulseBoard Channel Plugin\n\n**19 new files** under `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files modified.\n\n### Architecture\nPulseBoard supports `direct` (DMs) and `group` (boards) chat types with a 4000-char text limit. It uses a polling monitor (HTTP `GET /api/v1/updates`) for inbound messages and REST endpoints for outbound. The fictional client uses native `fetch` with Bearer auth — no external npm dependencies needed.\n\n### Key design decisions\n| Concern | Decision |\n|---|---|\n| Target format | `#boardname` → `board:boardname`, `@userid` / bare `userid` → `dm:userid` |\n| Text limit | 4000 chars, markdown chunker mode |\n| Delivery | `\"direct\"` mode, mirrors IRC |\n| DM policy | Full pairing / allowlist / open / disabled suite |\n| Monitor | HTTP poll every 2s, `AbortSignal`-driven teardown |\n| Multi-account | Yes, via `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter` (mirrors IRC) |\n\n### Files\n- **5 root files**: manifest, package.json, index.ts, setup-entry.ts, api.ts  \n- **14 source files**: types, config-schema (Zod), runtime store, runtime-api barrel, accounts, normalize, HTTP client stub, send, inbound, monitor, probe, setup-surface, channel (main plugin), tests\n\n### Flagged uncertainties\nThe plan notes 6 specific import paths that must be confirmed by reading `extensions/irc/src/runtime-api.ts` and related IRC files before writing the final code (e.g., exact subpath for `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase`, `PAIRING_APPROVED_MESSAGE`, `buildChannelConfigSchema`).\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm test -- extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.test.ts\npnpm check\n```",
